    {
      "id": "2037389198576275528",
      "text": "Starlink is actually that good",
      "created_at": "Fri Mar 27 04:40:12 +0000 2026",
      "lang": "en",
      "media": [],
      "retweet": null,
      "quoted": {
        "id": "2037310499050709412",
        "text": "Starlink in flight Wi-Fi review:\n\n\"I just tried Starlink Wi-Fi on United — and I can't believe they're not charging for this. This is a game changer. The experience itself was surprisingly seamless. Once I logged in on my phone, I used a QR code to connect my laptop instantly, because yes you can connect unlimited devices. I even uploaded a 40-second TikTok, something I’ve never attempted mid-flight because it usually requires leaving the app open and hoping it doesn’t fail. With Starlink, it took about five minutes and worked on the first try. I can guarantee I’ll notice the difference the next time I fly without Wi-Fi like I experienced on this flight.\"",
